A lazy way to spin up virtual machines to investigate PostgreSQL portability
problems on various OSes, with:

 * all needed packages
 * all needed OS configuration
 * PostgreSQL source tree cloned
 * configured, compiled, installed, ccache is prewarmed

Status:

debian11:    all options, 64 bit and 32 bit
freebsd12:   all options
netbsd9:     all options except gssapi
openbsd6:    all options except gssapi, llvm, nls
openindiana: all options except gssapi, llvm

